Tottenham will face Besiktas in the Europa League after north London rivals Arsenal relegated the Turkish club to European club football's second tier while Everton will contest a group including Wolfsburg and Lille after the draw in Monaco.

The Gunners just overcame the Istanbul side over two legs in the Champions League play-offs, with Slaven Bilic's side dropping down to become top seeds in the secondary competition. 

Also ahead of Mauricio Pochettino's side in group C is Serbia's Partizan Belgrade and Greek side Asteras. 

